        public boolean isEmote()

        Checks if this argument is in a valid Emote mention form. The result of this method is equivalent to checking this argument against a regex of <:.+:[0-9]+>

      • getEmote

        @NotNull
public net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.Emote getEmote()
        Description copied from interface: CommandArgument
        If CommandArgument.isEmote() would return true, this method will always return a not-null value, null otherwise. If the formatting is correct but JDA cannot resolve the Emote, a Fake Emote will be returned.

        If isEmote() would return true, it is guaranteed that this method returns a non-null value.

        Specified by:
        getEmote in interface CommandArgument
        Overrides:
        getEmote in class MentionArgument
        Returns:
        An Emote if the formatting is correct. Otherwise null.
